# Documentation & ADR Rules

## Code Documentation
- All public functions, classes, and modules must have comprehensive docstrings.
- Use JSDoc or TypeScript doc comments for frontend code.

## API Documentation
- API must be documented via OpenAPI/Swagger.
- All endpoints must have summary and description fields.

## ADRs
- Major architectural decisions must be recorded as ADRs in `architecture.mdc`.
- Use the provided ADR template for all new decisions.

## README
- All major components must have an up-to-date README file describing purpose, usage, and API.



